ool families access to education tax deduction\"], ''The Ripon Advance'', August 28, 2013. (Retrieved August 28, 2013)</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nCole and his wife, Ellen, have one son, Mason. He is a member of the [[United Methodist Church]] and lives in Moore.\n\nCole has said, \"I was raised to think of myself as Native American and, most importantly, as [[Chickasaw]].\"<ref name=\"LOCNativeAmericanKeynoteAddress\">{{cite speech\n | title = Native American Heritage Month Keynote Address\n | author =\n | first =\n | last =\n | authorlink =\n | date = 2007-11-06\n | location = Library of Congress\n | url = http://www.loc.gov/today/cyberlc/feature_wdesc.php?rec=4216\n | accessdate = 2008-09-01\n}}</ref>\n\nCole has said that a great-aunt of his was the Native American storyteller [[Te Ata Fisher|Te Ata]].<ref name=\"LOCNativeAmericanKeynoteAddress\"/>\n\nCole has said, \"... [My] mother Helen Cole<ref>[http://www.usao.edu/usao-news/spring-04/Obit_Sen_Helen_Cole.htm Helen Cole]</ref> was... extraordinarily proud of our Native American history and was, frankly, the first Native American woman ever elected to state senate in Oklahoma.\"<ref name=\"LOCNativeAmericanKeynoteAddress\"/>\n\nCole sits on the [[Smithsonian Institution]] Board of Regents and the National Fulbright Association.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tom Cole Full Biography|url=http://cole.house.gov/about-me/full-biography|website=Tom Cole U.S. Congressman|accessdate=3 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nCole is featured in the play ''[[Sliver of a Full Moon]]'' by Mary Kathryn Nagle for his role in the re-authorization of the [[Violence Against Women Act]] in 2013<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sliverofafullmoon.org/#!/6|title=sliver of a full moon|website=sliver of a full moon|language=en-US|access-date=2016-12-12}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n\n{{refend}}\n{{reflist|colwidth=50em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* [http://cole.house.gov/ Congressman Tom Cole] official U.S. House site\n* [http://w